# chuk-ai-session-manager

[![Python 3.11+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

**The easiest way to add conversation tracking to any AI application.**

Track conversations, monitor costs, and manage infinite context with just 3 lines of code. Built for production, designed for simplicity.

## ğŸš€ 30-Second Start

```bash
uv add chuk-ai-session-manager
```

```python
from chuk_ai_session_manager import track_conversation

# Track any AI conversation in one line
await track_conversation("Hello!", "Hi there! How can I help?")
```

That's it! ğŸ‰ Your conversation is now tracked with full observability.

## âœ¨ Why Choose CHUK?

- **ğŸ”¥ Stupidly Simple**: 3 lines to track any conversation
- **ğŸ’° Cost Smart**: Automatic token counting and cost tracking
- **â™¾ï¸ Infinite Context**: No more "conversation too long" errors
- **ğŸ”§ Any LLM**: Works with OpenAI, Anthropic, local models, anything
- **ğŸ“Š Full Observability**: See exactly what's happening in your AI app
- **ğŸš€ Production Ready**: Used in real applications, not just demos

